Haskell lists contain an indefinite number of elements of a single type. 
It is sometimes useful to create list-like functions that accept an indefinite
number of parameters of multiple types.

PolyToMonoid provides such a function, 'ptm' and a typeclass 'Monoidable'. 
The only precondition is that the parameters of 'ptm' can be mapped to an 
underlying monoid using the 'toMonoid' function provided by 'Monoidable'.